6th Match (D/N), Kuala Lumpur, Sep 22 2006, DLF Cup

Australia

213

India

(43.5/50 ov, target 214)195
Australia won by 18 runs
Player Of The Match
Brett Lee, AUS
5/38
Summary
Scorecard
Report
Commentary
Statistics
Overs
Table
News
Photos

Mongia is left stranded on 63 but you have to question his decision to keep taking singles and exposing the tailenders. It would have been commended had it come off but fact is that it didn't work.

Lee's fibe wickets came at all the right times He dismissed Tendulkar and Sehwag cheaply, came back and broke a threatening partnership by snaring Dhoni before returning at the death to snap up the tail. Mongia's 63 was the only meaningful contribution in the Indian innings.

Australia have won by 18 runs and have secured a place in Sunday's final againt West Indies. India on the other hand will be packing their bags to return home. It's been a very eventful day with more than a fair share of controversy. Do read S Rajesh's bulletin for more details.

Lee wins the Man-of-the-Match award for his searing spell. He deserves it too! A word though for Haddin and Hogg who came together when Australia were sinking at 117 for 6 and wrested the initiative from India with some superb and sensible strokeplay.

Well that's it from us at Cricinfo. Do join us on Sunday when Australia take on West Indies in the final. Cheers!
